Preliminary Wrangling¶

Wrangling was done in a seprate notebooks 'download and decompress data file.ipynb'

  • to download the compressed data file decompress it then save it

then 'data_cleaning.ipynb'

where the following was done:

1- The main flights data set &the supporting airports & carriers data sets were loaded
2- added Dest & the Destation & Origin cities, airports & states  columns containing iata data and rename iata to Origin for joining the main flights & airports tables 
3- Renamed Code column to UniqueCarrier and  Description to CarrierName for joining the main flights & carriers tables 
4- Dropped 'TailNum','FlightNum','Diverted', 'ActualElapsedTime','CRSElapsedTime','TaxiIn' & 'TaxiOut' colunms
5- Converted CRSArrTime, CRSDepTime, ArrTime & DepTime times to time string and gettig Dep & Arr hours
6- Converted CRSArrTime, CRSDepTime, ArrTime & DepTime string to timedelta
7- get the Origin & Destination airports, citys and states form airports data by joining the main flights & airports table
8- Get the flight CarrierName data by joining the main flights & carrier tables
9- saved the cleaned filghts data as 2008_cleaned.csv in data files folder

Introduction¶

This document explores a dataset that reports flights in the United States, including carriers, airports, times of sechedued and actual arrival and departure delays, and times of reasons for delays. It contains approximately 7,000,000 Flights in 2008.

# correct CRSArrTime, CRSDepTime, ArrTime and DepTime datatypes from object to timedelta
df_flights['CRSArrTime'] = pd.to_timedelta(df_flights['CRSArrTime'] )
df_flights['CRSDepTime'] = pd.to_timedelta(df_flights['CRSDepTime'])
df_flights['ArrTime'] = pd.to_timedelta(df_flights['ArrTime'] ,errors = 'coerce')
df_flights['DepTime'] = pd.to_timedelta(df_flights['DepTime'],errors = 'coerce')

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

Originally, there are 7,000,000 flights in the dataset with 22 features (Year, Month, DayofMonth, DayOfWeek, DepTime, CRSDepTime, ArrTime, CRSArrTime, UniqueCarrier, AirTime, ArrDelay, DepDelay, Origin, Dest, Distance, Cancelled, CancellationCode, Diverted, CarrierDelay, WeatherDelay, NASDelay, SecurityDelay & LateAircraftDelay)

Most features are numeric in nature (AirTime,Distance, ArrDelay, DepDelay, Diverted, CarrierDelay, WeatherDelay, NASDelay, SecurityDelay & LateAircraftDelay)), their are features of Categorical data type such as (Origin, Dest, Carriers, UniqueCarrier & CancellationCode. and Also we have date and time types such as( Year, Month, DayofMonth & DayOfWeek and DepTime , CRSDepTimeArrTime & CRSArrTime) and finally we have features of flag type such as (Cancelled & Diverted) where their values are 1 for Yes & 0 for No

We also had some additionally we had some other features that were removed during cleaning process such as (TailNum, FlightNum, Diverted, ActualElapsedTime, CRSElapsedTime, TaxiIn & TaxiOut) as they are werent contributing to my features of interest.

Then Iv add some features by joining with other table such as (Dest_airport, Dest_city, Dest_state, Origin_airport, Origin_city & Origin_state) from carrier table and (Carriers name) airport table.

Description of final features:¶

For time & date data:

  • Year, Month, DayofMonth & DayOfWeek: represent the date of the flight
  • ArrTime & CRSArrTime: represent the actual and scheduled arrival times of flights respectively
  • DepTime & CRSDepTime: represent the actual and scheduled departure hours of flights respectively

For Categorical data:

  • UniqueCarrier , Carriers are the Carrier Unique code and its name respectively
  • Dest_airport, Dest_city, Dest_state, Origin_airport, Origin_city & Origin_state are the filghts' destination & Origin airport, city & state respectively
  • Dest & Origin are the filghts' destination & Origin airports codes respectively
  • CancellationCode Specifies The Reason For Cancellation
  • Dest_airport, Dest_city, Dest_state, Origin_airport, Origin_city, Origin_state : Destination & Origin airports, cities and states receptively.
  • Carriers name : airline name

For flag type data:

  • Cancelled: if the flights was cancelled or not (1 for Yes & 0 for No)

And for numerical data:

  • ArrDelay, DepDelay are arrival & departure delaies in minutes respectively alongside with TotalDelay
  • CarrierDelay, WeatherDelay, NASDelay, SecurityDelay, LateAircraftDelay the amount delays due to diffrent delays reasons
  • Airtime: Flight Time, in Minutes
  • Distance Distance between airports (miles)

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I'm interested in finding out which contribute to the the main feature Depature Delay (DepDelay).

In this dataset I'm interested in answering the following questions:

  • what time of the year and day that flights are most likely to be dalayed?
  • which are the top 15 carrier that contribute the most to flights delays?
  • which are the top 15 airports that contribute the most to flights delays?
  • in which time of the year / states weather delays are most occring?

For the first question, the features will be flights Depature Delay (DepDelay), Flights month (Month), Day of Month (DayofMonth), Day of the week (DayOfWeek) & Depaturer hour (DepHour).

While for the the second question, the features will be flights airlines (CarrierName), Depature Delay (DepDelay), Airlines Delay (CarrierDelay) & Late Aircraft Delay (LateAircraftDelay).

And for the third question, the features will be flights Depature airlines (Origin_airport), Depature Delay (DepDelay)

For the forth question,the features will be flights Depature state (Origin_state), weather delay (WeatherDelay) , Flights month (Month), Day of Month (DayofMonth).
